>
> Well, just speculation on my part - I am no professional in this area.
> However, did he discuss _how_ common it is ?  Just because it is common
> does not mean it is the norm.  

This is common in nearsighted persons.  One tends to farsightedness in ones 
older age.  For a nearsighted person, that equates to vision closer to 
nominal.  It happened to my mother, and judging by the relative flatness of 
my prescription over the last 7 years (compared with the previous 30), it 
will happen to me.

